<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=973143005610></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f973143005610><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=7&mid=973143005610>RE: What to keep in your spell slots?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=7&mid=973143005610#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43><span id=Sage>Waeloga</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>56 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Nov 2nd 12:30 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At Level 26, I always keep the following:<br>Devine Aura, bravery, Spirit Armour, G. Heal, Heal. Now the "last" 3 are all situational<br>Smite, Stun, Holy might. This is my "general" selection (if with a Druid or Ranger (their Snare is better than Root I feel))<br><br>If vs Undead? Drop Smite for our Undead nukes..<br><br>There is so many possible combos that you as a cleric need to know where, how and what you're going to face so you can make the correct choices... Facing Poison using creatures (in Splitpaw Hall trash?) then mem resist poison, buff everyone with it and exchange it for Counteract poison as a ready spell. It all depends on where you are<br><br>Waerloga (who day 1 mis-spelt his name... grin)<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
